name: Rumkigr Tonnipar
text: The Papa John's Pizza was amazing! Ordered the sausage, bell peppers, and black olive pizza, minus the mushrooms. The sausage mixed perfectly with the other ingredients and the hearty tomato sauce. If you love Zachary's Pizza in Berkeley, CA, you'll love Little Star.

text: Their pizza has recently taken a turn for the worse, thin crust, little sauce, etc. They can't handle rushes, they hire teens who don't care about the business or customer service and think it's OK to curse at you because they're …More

name: Agent of Hydra
text: Food was fine but they forgot my 2 liter smh.

name: GW Parker
text: Its good pizza. I say that because I know what great pizza is. (Gondolas, Blackjacks) and for quick take out its pretty good.

name: Carol Porter
text: Sometimes the service is good. I think they must have a high turnover of employees. On a late Friday afternoon, I kept calling & it would ring & ring & ring... I finally went in, (I was trying to order so I could quickly pick it up on my …More

name: Troy Worrell
text: The pizza is not cheap and it is very dry. I guess this is normal for places like this, but there was very little sauce and I paid for extra meat, but it had about the same amount as a normal pizza if not even a bit less.

name: sunil vij
text: The guy working on 3pm shift has no respects for time. While I placed my order 15 minutes ago. He is on phone and has not even put the pizza in the oven. It's not a rush time and no other customer except me here. Made me wait to long...

name: Mike Galindo
text: Love the pizza. Great service too.

name: J M
text: Fast service - delicious pizza; the garlic sauce is what's up.

name: James Heizer
text: I like their pizza. Today they told me they shut their phone off when they get busy. So I drove down in two minutes and waited 20 minutes for the pizza.

name: Sean Crossman
text: Girl on phone was extremely rude.
